items.text:
Science Boffins is currently looking for more phenomenal Science Boffins to help us to bring science to life for primary school children. We have schools booked during British Science Week which runs from 9th to 13th March as well as party/events throughout the year.

You don't need a formal background in science as we teach you everything you'll need to know.

All you need is access to a car (unless London based), the ability to work some weekends/weekdays and the desire to launch rockets, concoct potions and generally share just how much fun science can be.

HOW DOES BEING A SCIENCE BOFFIN WORK?

For the right person, this could be the most fun way of making an extra income.

You'll get to enjoy inspiring and educating children, having a fantastic time and getting paid along the way. You'll travel to an event in your local area and bring science to life for primary school age children with some brilliant science experiments.

Are you a fun, enthusiastic and reliable person and able to communicate effectively and promptly to potential bookings? Then join a nationwide team of 40+ well-paid Science Boffin presenters.  We have a strong reputation, rave reviews, and the privilege of working with some globally recognised companies.

We're a friendly bunch and have a (we think!) cracking training program to help you get up to speed. If that sounds like you? You too can become one of our amazing Science Boffins and bring science alive to children.

Looking forward to hearing from you.

Annette

Science Boffins

items.title: Greetings all,

items.text:
**VACANCY - Acting Teacher**

North West End Acting School is a Spotlight-approved establishment based in Chester, focused acting training for adults and teens, plus workshops, 1-2-1 training, singing lessons, and performances. Our students have gone onto study at some of the most prestigious drama schools in the country, as well as taking on acting roles in a range of television programmes. Lead by Lucy Thatcher, known for being in the original cast of the RSC‚Äôs *Matilda* in London‚Äôs West End, the school is expanding and we are searching for a part-time acting teacher to come on board and help us teach our adult group acting classes. 

The skills we're looking for:
* Acting teaching experience for adults (18+)
* Professional acting training
* Professional acting experience in theatre and TV
* Experience in working to lesson plans and/or a curriculum
* Be enthusiastic, energetic and friendly
* Can teach techniques and exercises from - Meisner, Uta Hagen, Stanislavski

The post holder will also be responsible for the welfare of the students and the opening and closing of the venue.

Candidates should be DBS checked and have Public Liability Insurance.

A bit more about the role:

Classes take place in Chester between 7:15pm and 9:15pm and run over a period of ten weeks. You will be working with groups of maximum 20 students. The courses run regularly throughout the year. The role is paid ¬£25 per hour.

We are looking for someone who is dynamic and adaptable, able to work with a variety of people from all backgrounds and ages and with a passion for sharing the joy of acting.

TO APPLY:

Please send us a CV and cover letter detailing how your experience suits the job description. Do send us a Spotlight link or anything you think relevant to your professional acting experience.
* Contact name: Agathe Rault
* Contact email: info@northwestendactingschool.co.uk

https://www.northwestendactingschool.co.uk/

If AI already has your attention as an actor, this is your heads-up.

From 25 December, an Intro video will go on @theactorscopilot ‚Äì created for actors who want to use AI to enhance their work, not replace it.

You can watch it in your own time, replay it, and sit with what it means for your auditions, your self-tapes, and your career.

Inside, we‚Äôll share a first look at a new way for actors to:
‚Ä¢ save time on prep,
‚Ä¢ go deeper into performance, and
to 'create ‚Ä¢ perform ‚Ä¢ produce' on their own terms.

Watch the video from Dec 25th
Decide for yourself.

Pilotfilm + 20 Folgen Staffel 1 + langfristige Serienplanung.

Wir reden nicht. Wir drehen.

Und daf√ºr suchen wir JETZT:

üëâ 1. Ein Produktionsstudio, das Action kann

üëâ 2. Schauspielerinnen & Schauspieler, die Bock auf gro√üe Rollen haben

WAS EUCH ERWARTET:

Real-Action statt Sci-Fi: Fahrzeuge, Taktik, Stunts ‚Äì alles echt.

Hauptfahrzeug: Chevrolet Camaro ‚ÄûCODE RED‚Äú

Klare Story, fertige Struktur, professionelles Team

**CASTING CALL ‚Äî Vancouver, BC**
Looking for actors (18+) to play *16‚Äì18* for a 4th-year Capilano University short film titled **BOYISH**.

A coming-of-age story about the messy shift from boyhood to adulthood, dumb dares, and the people we meet along the way.

**ROLES:**
**LUKA (lead)** ‚Äî male-presenting, playing 16‚Äì18. Quiet, awkward, observant.
**YAZ (lead)** ‚Äî male-presenting, playing 16‚Äì18. Bright, restless, warm.

**Union + Non-Union welcome (volunteer)**
**Filming:** Feb 7‚Äì9, 2026 (Vancouver)
**Actors must be 18+**

To submit, send headshot + reel to **boyish2026@gmail.com** by **Dec 1st, 2025 ‚Äì 11:59pm**.
Subject line: **BOYISH ‚Äì LUKA** or **BOYISH ‚Äì YAZ**

We have had many success stories over the years. Here are a few examples from students attending our courses. 

- Billie May Verity attended our Emmerdale course and was cast as Beth's auntie in Emmerdale.
- Amy Jo Clough attended a Hollyoaks course and was cast as Cassie.
- Josh Clayton auditioned for a featured role in Emmerdale and reached the final two candidates.
- Chrissy Parle attended the Kate Bone course and was cast in the BBC's The Responder. 

Our next adult acting course is a 4 week course for actors age 16+. In the final week, the actors will perform in a mock casting in front of Award winning Hollyoaks Casting Director Peter Hunt. Peter will give feedback, notes and direction on each individual performance.

 We have had a great success rate from previous Hollyoak's Courses. 

The fee is ¬£145

Studio 96, Salford, Media City, M50 2GZ

Ballet Cymru are seeking exceptional and diverse dancers with excellent Classcal Ballet and/or Contemporary and Creative Skills. 

Full time and freelance contracts available, starting April 2026.

To Apply
Please send your details in the form of a written CV or preferred presentation, along with links to suitable photos and/or videos to:

Darius James OBE, Artistic Director Ballet Cymru

Email: dariusjames@welshballet.co.uk

Auditions by invitation only will be held in Ballet Cymru‚Äôs accessible dance studios in Newport, Wales, UK in February 2026.

EURASIA AUDITION WINNERS
üìç SRI LANKA - ASIA

Who are the 2025  EurAsia Audition Winners selected among the students that last week attended the EurAsia Auditions on tour in Colombo and Jaffna, Sri Lanka?

In the next weeks we will announce the names of the EurAsia Audition Winners with their related EurAsia Scholarships and destinations in Europe.

The lectures and the masterclasses have been brought on tour in the country for the University of Jaffna, the EurAsia Partner MeshGround - A Platform For Movement Arts of Colombo and for the University of the Visual and Performing Arts of Colombo.

Also this second tour in Sri Lanka have been brought by EurAsia Dance Project International Network ETS, directed by Stefano Fardelli, supported by the Italian Embassy of Colombo, Sri Lanka.

In 2026, along with the workshops and the auditions, the shows of the E.D.C. - EurAsia Dance Company on tour in the country.

items.text:
Hi everyone, I hope it‚Äôs okay to share this here.

We‚Äôve just opened applications for our 2026 TMA Collective Programme, running on **Sundays** 11th January - 29th March, and I wanted to share it for any parents of young performers aged 15‚Äì20 who may be looking for the next step in their training.

This age group can often be overlooked as they‚Äôre too old for child casting, not yet in full-time drama school, and often juggling GCSEs/college with fewer audition opportunities, which is exactly why we designed this programme specifically for them.

Across 12 Sunday sessions, students receive:

**‚ú® Drama school & audition preparation**

**‚ú® On-camera training + a fully edited showreel**

**‚ú® Professional headshots**

**‚ú® West End & industry guest tutors**

**‚ú® Agency mentoring with current industry knowledge**

**‚ú® And importantly, all attendees are considered for representation with **Tucker Management

We‚Äôve also been supported by Innovate UK, which allows us to offer five fully-funded scholarship places for young performers from low-income households across the Midlands.

üìÖ Applications close 30th November

üé≠ We‚Äôre looking for potential, passion, and dedication, not perfection.

If you‚Äôd like more information or to register interest, you can do that on our website:

[[https://www.tuckermgmt.uk/tma-collective](https://www.tuckermgmt.uk/tma-collective)](https://www.tuckermgmt.uk/tma-collective)

And please feel free to DM me with any questions, I‚Äôm happy to help!

Ruby

TMA founder & Senior Agent at TM Talent Agency

sharedPost.text:
We have had many success stories over the years. Here are a few examples from students attending our courses. 

- Billie May Verity attended our Emmerdale course and was cast as Beth's auntie in Emmerdale.
- Amy Jo Clough attended a Hollyoaks course and was cast as Cassie.
- Josh Clayton auditioned for a featured role in Emmerdale and reached the final two candidates.
- Chrissy Parle attended the Kate Bone course and was cast in the BBC's The Responder. 

Our next adult acting course is a 4 week course for actors age 16+. In the final week, the actors will perform in a mock casting in front of Award winning Hollyoaks Casting Director Peter Hunt. Peter will give feedback, notes and direction on each individual performance.

 We have had a great success rate from previous Hollyoak's Courses. 

The fee is ¬£145

Studio 96, Salford, Media City, M50 2GZ

if you would like to book your place please click the link below:

https://screenplayacting.com/product/hollyoaks-course-january-2026/

üì¢ LAST CALL ‚Äì Letzte M√∂glichkeit, sich zu melden!

10.01.2026
Eine √úbernachtung am 10.01. ist selbstverst√§ndlich m√∂glich.
üí∏ Gage: 100 ‚Ç¨
‚ùó Fahrtkosten und Verpflegung sind nicht enthalten, da das Projekt komplett privat finanziert wird.
Die √úbernachtung wird jedoch √ºbernommen.
üìç Wo?
N√∂rdlingen, Landkreis Donau-Ries
üé≠ Wer?
Rolle: Sam (3 Szenen)
Gesucht wird eine Schauspielerin (18‚Äì35 Jahre) mit sehr gutem oder akzentfreiem Englisch und einem jugendlichen Erscheinungsbild (die Charaktere sind Teenager).
Idealerweise mit F√ºhrerschein, da ich leider schlechte Erfahrungen mit Drehtagen und Bahnverbindungen gemacht habe. Falls es anders nicht geht, kann ich mir dar√ºber noch Gedanken machen.
üßç‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è Kurzbeschreibung der Rolle ‚ÄûSam‚Äú:
Sam ist ein ganz normales, freundliches Teenager-M√§dchen, das viel lacht, offen ist und es liebt, in die Kamera zu sprechen.
üé¨ Kurze Beschreibung zum Projekt:
Nole und Sam m√ºssen f√ºr ein Schulprojekt einen Kurzfilm drehen. Doch das Kost√ºm von Blackbird erwacht zum Leben und beginnt, die beiden gnadenlos zu verfolgen.
Der Film wird auch im Lost-&-Found-Footage-Stil gedreht.
üí° √úber mich:
Ich bin ein noch sehr unerfahrener, fast schon amateurhafter Filmemacher und habe bisher vier kurze Filme auf meinem YouTube-Kanal ver√∂ffentlicht.
Wenn ihr nach gro√üen Projekten f√ºr euer Portfolio sucht, ist das hier vermutlich nicht das Richtige.
Das Drehbuch ist bereits fertig und ich zeige es euch gerne bei Interesse.

Da es um Five Nights at Freddy‚Äôs geht und die Fanbase sehr gro√ü ist, hoffe ich dennoch, dass der Film viele Klicks bekommen wird ‚Äì es bleibt aber klar ein Hobbyprojekt.
Der fertige Film wird auf YouTube ver√∂ffentlicht.

üëâ Ich freue mich sehr auf eure Nachrichten! üòÉ

VANCOUVER CREATORS ‚Äî CASTING NOW üé¨

Fourth Frame Media is making a bold new social series that explores identity, groupthink, and how we judge others. If you‚Äôre vibrant, curious, and outspoken, we want you on camera. Filming is in Vancouver, BC (local talent only).

Volunteer-based, and the winner takes home a prize.

Topics we‚Äôre shooting:

* Do I Look Like My Job?

* Best Friend Chooses Your Partner ‚Äî Person Seeking Partner

* Is the Canadian Dream Still Alive?

* Match 30 people to their jobs

* Can People Match Your Income to You?

Apply here: https://www.4thframemedia.com/casting

Please share with friends in Vancouver who‚Äôd love this!

items.text:
CASTING CALL

As You Like It by William Shakespeare 
Directed by Bronwen Maeve and Hannah Scott

The Shakespeare All Year Theatre Society would love to encourage all to submit for our upcoming production of As You Like It set at a Renaissance Festival! The Bard‚Äôs enduring comedy brought to life in a Vancouver heritage building. 

Submission Deadline: Dec 7th 11:59pm

Audition dates: Jan 4th and 6th

Rehearsals: Wednesday evening and Saturday or Sunday afternoon

Show dates: April 30th - May 16th

Please Submit a Headshot and Resume to saysociety24@gmail.com
Subject line: As You Like It Submission - [FIRST AND LAST NAME]
Please include which character(s) you are submitting for, if any in mind.
Please submit for any role regardless of suggested age or gender.

ANIMA ECLIPTICA ‚Äî Sacred Small Circle (Sunday 23. November, Berlin)

A night for those who feel the call.
Shadow. Light. Truth.
A living theatre where your inner self becomes visible.

This is not a public event.
It is a protected circle, limited seats, intimate, guided with deep presence and Hands of Light.
Only for those truly ready to step into their inner portal.

Reservation is required.

Acting in Longer Form ‚Äì with Arek Ziƒôtek

Ready to take your acting and improv to the next level and bring real stories to life on stage? This workshop is all about longer scenes, deeper characters, and authentic storytelling, guided by Arek Ziƒôtek, one of Warsaw‚Äôs most respected theatre improvisers and teachers.

Arek has worked with Keith Johnstone, the father of modern improvisation, and now he‚Äôs sharing that knowledge in this unique advanced workshop for experienced performers.

You‚Äôll explore long-form improvisation techniques, learn to build emotional depth in your characters, and discover how to create stories that feel real, funny, and moving, all in English.

üëâ Important: This is not for beginners. You‚Äôll need some previous acting or improv experience and a confident level of English. We‚Äôre keeping the group small so everyone gets space, feedback, and focus.

Why join?
‚ú® Learn from one of Poland‚Äôs top improv teachers.
‚ú® Master storytelling through longer scenes and strong relationships.
‚ú® Work in English with passionate, international performers.
‚ú® Grow your stage presence and confidence in a supportive circle.

Schedule & Pricing
üìÜ Starting: Tuesday, November 25th
‚è∞ 7:00 PM
üìç Atlas Tower ‚Äì al. Jerozolimskie 123A, Warsaw

üéüÔ∏è Limited Spots:
First 5 applicants: 300 PLN (full 4-week course)
Next 5 spots: 350 PLN

If more than 10 apply, we might open a second group, but no promises!

Join us for a deep, fun, and creative exploration of what it means to truly act and improvise in longer form.

Very Limited Spots https://fienta.com/pl/acting-storytelling-improv-workshop-with-arek-zietek-155700

**CASTING CALL!**

Hello everyone! My name is Sofia Vargas and I‚Äôm the Producer for the UNCSA third year film, *Metanoia*. We are casting our lead characters!

Story: On the last night of Mariana‚Äôs visit to her brother Mateo in the U.S., the two Latin American siblings are pushed into unfamiliar territory when a moment of discovery at a Latin club gives Mariana a glimpse of who she truly is. Together, they navigate the fragile, unspoken shifts in identity, desire, and growing up that both pull them apart and draw them closer.

We are accepting auditions submissions! Character Breakdowns are attached. If you‚Äôre interested in auditioning for these roles, send your **name, age, pronouns,** **headshot, and role preference  **to [metanoiafilmcasting@gmail.com](mailto:metanoiafilmcasting@gmail.com) for audition materials! 

The **interest deadline **is December 1st! 

Production title: Metanoia 

Union / Non-Union: Non-Union

Director: Mart√≠n Collo Sastoque

Filming: January and February 2026

Shooting Location: Winston-Salem, NC

We look forward to seeing your audition!

2 DAYS LEFT TO RSVP---> QR Code & LINK Below - YOU'RE INVITED THIS SUNDAY ü•ÇCelebrating the contributions of our actors and networking with other industry peers ‚Äì Flink Appreciation Event, November 30th @3pm (WestChase)

We're opening registration, and you're invited! Take a quick minute today to secure your spot using the link below:

RSVP Link: PAUSE QR CODE https://forms.gle/GhutENbwc6vpXBLm9

Bringing a friend or inviting a peer? Make sure they register as well. Every attendee needs their own RSVP so we can prepare properly and make sure everyone has the full experience.

We are celebrating viral talent that has surpassed 100K+ views and bringing together creators, performers, directors, casting professionals, and industry players for a night of connection and inspiration.

sydneejane@flinkbrandcoach.com #flinkhonors #flinkhouston #flinkusa #flinksoiree

We are giving rising talent their flowers. The Viral Stars & Honors Soir√©e is coming, and we are celebrating actors and digital creators who didn‚Äôt just go viral, but made real impact with 100K+ views and performances people could not scroll past.

This is not a regular industry mixer. It is a night of recognition, community, and opportunity with creators, actors, directors, casting contacts, marketing professionals, and digital storytellers all in one room. Expect real networking, genuine connection, a talent honors presentation, light bites, refreshments, karaoke, crystal giveaways, and the option to stay for a discounted murder mystery experience after 4 PM.

If you are looking to enter acting, grow as a creator, expand your network, or finally step into spaces that can open doors, this is your sign to show up.

Business Cocktail Attire
RSVP Required

Tonight and tomorrow only at No Square Theatre in Laguna Beach!

Get your tickets at: [https://www.tix.com/ticket-sales/nosquare/1804](https://www.tix.com/ticket-sales/nosquare/1804?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExdE9CMUlNdmlWaHQ1Z0hXRHNydGMGYXBwX2lkDzUxNDc3MTU2OTIyODA2MQABHhigjsOFZIS1vnXu10jY_YsHWJ5nXvz5lgiqWRc5_TvZ_pxZxMayZs6Vc-tX_aem_Qgp-5aGk8mHoi59iA-L5bQ)

SHE KILLS MONSTERS: YOUNG ADVENTURERS EDITION, a play by Qui Nguyen and directed by No Square Theatre Artistic Director, Joe Lauderdale, tells the story of high schooler Agnes Evans as she deals with the death of her younger sister, Tilly. When Agnes finds Tilly‚Äôs Dungeons & Dragons notebook, she gets pulled into an exciting adventure in the imaginary world that was her sister‚Äôs escape. The story is a thrilling, fast-paced dramatic comedy laden with homicidal fairies, nasty ogres, and ‚Äô90s pop culture celebrating both the geek and the warrior inside all of us.

November 22 & 23 Only!

Der Kino Mittwoch auf radioYpsilon 

MOVIETIME KW 48/2025

ALLTAG EINER EHE UND DER ANIMATIONSHIT DES JAHRES

9 Jahre ist es her, nun ermitteln Judy Hopps und Nick Wilde erneut  in ZOOMANIA 2 (Stadtkinocenter Laa,  Babylon Kino Horn und Filmb√ºhne Waidhofen/Ybbs).

Den Alltag eines Ehepaares nach vielen gemeinsamen Beziehungsjahren bringt uns Neele Leana Vollmar empathisch auf die Leinwand. So nebenbei durften wir auch mit der Regisseurin ein paar Worte wechseln.

Ausserdem gibt es noch eine Doppelconferance im Interview mit Cynthia Erivo und Ariana Grande sowie erz√§hlt uns Rick Kavanian √ºber die Arbeit als Synchronsprecher zum neuesten Disney Zeichentrick Blockbuster.

Weitere Filmtipps wie zb aus dem Kronenkino Mistelbach und Musik aus 80 Jahren Moviehistory pr√§sentiert Ihnen Sarah Fuchs. 

Mittwoch 26.11.25 von 18 bis 19h auf radioYpsilon 94.5 oder via Stream (http://mp3.radioypsilon.at:8000/)

items.text:
Hi Everyone! I run a nonprofit that provides children who have lost a parent or sibling with a special gift or experience to help them on their grief journey. In June 2026 we are hosting a 5-day free theater day-camp in Boulder for these bereaved children. We are partnering with an Atlanta-based theater company, Destination Theatre. If you or someone you know has a child who would qualify, please feel free to share this information with them. More info is on our website and application. Statistically 1 in 12 children will lose a parent or sibling by the time they are an adult so it is quite possible someone knows someone who would benefit from this experience.  I will be posting this in several groups, so you may see this again!

Take care!

üé¨** Bad at Hellos Worse at Goodbyes: WORLDWIDE CASTING CALL **üáµüá≠

We are urgently seeking **experienced male actors (ages 31-49)** for the upcoming project, **"Bad at Hellos Worse at Goodbyes"**! Filming will take place in the **Philippines**.

We are specifically targeting actors who hold **German, British, Czech, or American** citizenship/nationality.

**Project & Role Details**

* **Project Title:** Bad at Hellos Worse at Goodbyes

items.text:
Hello All,
We are looking for an **actor for creative UGC** (User-Generated Content) to produce engaging, relatable, and authentic video content for Helmit, a parental control app designed to protect children from harassment, predators, and cyberbullying online. Our AI analyzes social media activity privately on the device and alerts parents only when there is a potential threat. Our mission is to educate families about online safety, cyberbullying, and protecting kids in the digital world.

**Who We Are Looking For**

- Parent, preferably female, age 35 or above

- English speaking preferred, German possible as well

- Comfortable speaking on camera

- Able to create warm, natural, storytelling style content

- A parent who understands real challenges in raising kids today

- Being a parent would be perfect, but not absolutely necessary

- Ideally located in Munich or the surrounding area

- 1 day of filming

**Topics include**

- Parenting education

- Parenting stories and experiences

- Light, natural mentions of our app when relevant

- scripts will be provided by us

- You may adjust the script wording to match your tone, voice, and natural speaking style

- You do not need to involve your kids. We want great parents to be part of the project, not the children

All content will be posted by our team on Helmit‚Äôs various social media channels

**What We Value**

Our main goal is to work closely with parents so we can better understand real challenges, create relatable educational content, and continue building our product to support families more effectively.

**Application - **Please include

- Samples of your previous video work

- A brief introduction about yourself and your parenting experience

If you love storytelling, creating honest content, and want to help build a safer digital world for kids, we would love to work with you. Please contact via email: [Niklas@helmit.org](mailto:Niklas@helmit.org)

More information about us: [www.helmit.org](http://www.helmit.org)

**CASTING CALL: LIVE SHOW HOSTS**

Los Angeles (Hollywood Studio)

**Firework** is seeking energetic, camera-ready **Live Show Hosts** to lead interactive livestream product demonstrations!

**PAY:** $25-$40/hour (based on experience)

**ROLE DETAILS:**
* Host live product shows from our Hollywood, CA studio
* Present tech & lifestyle products in an authentic, conversational style
* Work as freelance/1099 with potential to transition to part-time employee
* Average 5-10 hours/week (rarely exceeds 15 hours)
* Mostly weekdays, 8 AM - 8 PM PT

**WE'RE LOOKING FOR:**
* Strong on-camera presence & natural speaking ability
* Reliable, punctual, professional
* Available weekdays during business hours
* Prior hosting/livestream/UGC/acting experience preferred but not required

**AUDITION OPTIONS:**

**Option 1: On-Site Audition**
* Dates: December 10-11, 2025
* Time: 10 AM - 1 PM PT
* 10-15 min audition (3-min one-take hosting scenario)

**Option 2: Self-Tape Submission**
* Deadline: December 11, 2025 (11:59 PM PT)
* 3 minutes, vertical, one continuous take
* Host any tech/electronic product as if live
* Email to: Kimmy@fireworkhq.com
* Subject: [Your Name] ‚Äì Live Show Host Submission - LA Digital Showroom Host - Self Tape Submission

**TO APPLY:** [https://jobs.lever.co/fireworkhq/cd7d4561-4c57-4260-b880-8000a95f6f44](https://jobs.lever.co/fireworkhq/cd7d4561-4c57-4260-b880-8000a95f6f44)

* Work as freelance/1099 with potential to transition to part-time employee

Now casting couples in mixed orientation relationships for a new documentary series with a major cable network.

Mixed orientation relationships, often known as lavender partnerships, involve two partners who differ in their sexual orientation. We want to hear from couples who live together, share a daily life, and are engaged, married, or soon to be engaged.

This series will explore how couples navigate identity, commitment, outside expectations, and the realities of loving in a way that challenges societal norms.

If this describes you or someone you know, you can share your story at the link below.

mixedorientationcasting.castingcrane.com
